                          information from the web, it helps users save significant time and effort. The tool is capable of parsing 
                          and retrieving various types of content, such as html, css, js, images, videos, audios, etc</div>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-neon-red/50 mb-4 space-y-2 font-mono">
                        <li>• Version 1</li>
                        <li>• Scrape any website you want</li>
                        <li>• Get all html, css, js files etc</li>
                        <li>• 2x more faster than any other tool</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="mt-4 text-neon-red font-mono text-lg">Free</div>
                    <a href="https://github.com/greenbugx/WebScrapper">
                        <button class="w-full mt-4 p-3 bg-black border border-neon-red text-neon-red font-mono hover:bg-neon-red hover:text-black transition-all duration-300 rounded group-hover:animate-pulse cursor-pointer">
                            Get now
                        </button>
                    </a>
                </div>

                <!-- Security Training -->
                <div class="product-card opacity-0 translate-y-4 bg-black p-6 rounded border border-neon-red/20 hover:border-neon-red transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-1 relative group cursor-pointer">
                    <div class="text-neon-red text-xl mb-2 font-mono">Web Scrapperv2</div>
                    <div class="text-neon-red/60 mb-4 font-mono">The <b>Web Scrapper v2.1</b> is a Python-based tool designed to scrape 
                        and download entire websites, including all associated assets like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, images, 
                        videos, audios, and fonts. It leverages both <b>requests</b> and <b>Selenium</b> to handle dynamic content 
                        and provides advanced features for recursive crawling, user-agent spoofing, and error handling.</div>
                    <ul class="text-sm text-neon-red/50 mb-4 space-y-2 font-mono">
                        <li>• Version 2</li>
                        <li>• Scrape the entire website</li>
                        <li>• Uses Proxies & UserAgents</li>
                        <li>• 4x more faster than version 1</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="text-neon-red font-mono text-lg">Free</div>
                    <a href="https://github.com/greenbugx/WebScrapperv2">
                        <button class="w-full mt-4 p-3 bg-black border border-neon-red text-neon-red font-mono hover:bg-neon-red hover:text-black transition-all duration-300 rounded group-hover:animate-pulse cursor-pointer">
                            Get now
                        </button>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <footer class="py-8 text-center bg-black border-t border-neon-red/20">
            <p class="text-neon-red/40 font-mono">For detailed pricing and custom solutions, contact our team</p>
            <a href="mailto:silentcode@privatemx.org" class="text-neon-red font-mono hover:text-neon-red/80">
                silentcode@privatemx.org
            </a>
        </footer>
    </div>
</Layout>

<script>
    // Intersection Observer for fade-in animation
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
        entries.forEach((entry, index) => {
            if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                // Add delay based on index for staggered animation
                setTimeout(() => {
                    entry.target.classList.add('fade-in');
                }, index * 200); // 200ms delay between each card
            }
        });
    }, {
        threshold: 0.1,
        rootMargin: '50px'
    });

    // Observe all product cards
    document.querySelectorAll('.product-card').forEach(card => {
        observer.observe(card);
    });
</script>

<style>
    .product-card {
        transition: opacity 0.6s ease-out, transform 0.6s ease-out;
    }

    .product-card.fade-in {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateY(0);
    }
</style>